UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Bachelor of Education (Primary) is a pre-service teaching degree that prepares you to teach students from Prep to Grade 6. It is accredited by the Tasmanian Teachers Registration Board and recognised in all Australian states and territories. Once you graduate, you’ll be qualified to teach anywhere in Australia.</div><p><strong>What you’ll learn</strong></p><p>Throughout your degree, you’ll explore core teaching theory and evidence-based practice. You’ll examine child development and behaviour and study the subjects you’ll teach in the classroom.</p><p>Your learning will focus strongly on literacy, including speaking, listening, reading and writing. You’ll also develop skills across Mathematics, Science, Health and Physical Education, Art and Music.</p><p><strong>Build broad curriculum knowledge</strong></p><p>Primary teachers often teach multiple subjects to the same class. This course builds a strong foundation across the full curriculum. In your first two years, you’ll explore teaching fundamentals and gain skills in English, numeracy, arts, HPE and humanities. Later, you’ll select a teaching proficiency to deepen your expertise in a specific learning area.<br/><br/><strong>Inclusive, connected and future focused</strong></p><p>You’ll learn that teaching is not just about subjects. It is also about building strong relationships. Our curriculum emphasises inclusivity, wellbeing, sustainability, and Indigenous perspectives across all areas of study. We prepare you to support learners with diverse needs and to work in a wide range of community settings.</p><p><strong>Gain real-world experience</strong></p><p>As part of your course, you’ll complete 80 days of Professional Experience placements. These give you the chance to put your knowledge into practice in a safe, supportive classroom environment.</p><p><strong>Study your way</strong></p><p>This degree is available online across Australia, and on campus in Launceston and at Cradle Coast. You can study full-time or part-time, with flexible options to suit your lifestyle.</p><p><strong>Commonwealth Teaching Scholarships</strong></p><p>You could be eligible for up to $40,000 from the Australian Government to support your studies through the Commonwealth Teaching Scholarships Program. This initiative is designed to attract high-achieving and passionate individuals to the teaching profession, whether you are a school leaver or changing careers.</p><p>The scholarship supports both undergraduate and postgraduate students enrolled in initial teacher education (ITE) programs, helping to ease the cost of study. In return, you will commit to teaching in a government school or government-run early learning setting for a period equal to the length of your course.</p><p>With up to 1,000 scholarships available each year until 2028, it is a great time to begin your journey toward a rewarding career in education.</p><p>Apply using the online form at <a href="https://www.education.gov.au/teaching-scholarships" rel="external" target="_blank">education.gov.au/teaching-scholarships</a></p><p>For other University of Tasmania scholarships, visit our <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/scholarships-fees-and-costs">scholarships page</a>.</p><hr/><h5>Watch our course information webinar</h5><p>Thinking of studying this course and want to learn more? This webinar explores course structures, career opportunities, and the student experience to support your study journey.</p><p><a href="https://youtu.be/vliK5mk7gmk?si=9Ius1ElJUxBtnQPq" target="_blank" title="Watch our webinar">Watch now</a></p> </div>',
    total_course_duration = 'Minimum 4 years, up to a maximum of 9 years.',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '157104',
    entry_requirements = '<div class="accordion--content"> <p>All international students will need to meet the minimum English Language Requirements, University General Entry Requirements and any course specific requirements such as pre-requisite subjects, if applicable.</p> <p><strong>English Language Requirements</strong></p> <p>This degree requires an IELTS (Academic) of Overall IELTS Score of 7.5 (Writing and Reading no band less than 7.0, Listening and Speaking no band less than 8.0). PTE Academic is not accepted for this course.</p> <p>For students who do not meet the English Language Requirement through citizenship or prior studies in English in an approved country, evidence of an approved English language test completed within the last 2 years must be provided. See the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/international/applying/entry-requirements/english-language-requirements">English Language Requirements</a> page for more information.</p> <p><strong>General Entry Requirements</strong></p> <p>Admission to undergraduate courses at the University of Tasmania requires the completion of qualifications equivalent to a 12th year of education in Australia.</p> <p>Please review the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/international/applying/entry-requirements/equivalent-undergraduate-entry-requirements-by-country">equivalent undergraduate entry requirements</a> to see the minimum requirement relevant to your country. The ATAR information for this course is located in the “For Domestic Students” section of the entry requirements on this page.</p> <p>You can also meet the General Entry Requirement for this course with the following qualifications or prior studies:</p> <ul> <li>Completion of an equivalent AQF Certificate IV or above</li> <li>Complete or incomplete (minimum 25 credit points) of previous tertiary study at Bachelor level or higher</li> </ul> <p>If you do not meet the minimum requirements, we offer the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/acad/courses/x0f-foundation-studies-program-standard">Foundation Studies Program.</a></p> <p><strong>Course Specific Requirements</strong></p> <p>In addition, all applicants are required to provide a non-academic personal statement which is used to assist in the selection of students into all Initial Teacher Education (ITE) courses at the University of Tasmania.</p> <p>This statement is submitted through the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/education/student-resources/non-academic-capability">Non-Academic Capability Assessment Tool (NACAT)</a> after you have completed your application and is used in conjunction with your ATAR score (or equivalent alternative entry). <strong>All applicants must satisfactorily complete the NACAT before they will be provided with an offer into the course.</strong></p> <p>Instructions on submitting your statement and completing the NACAT are provided during the application process.</p> <p><strong>Literacy and Numeracy Test for Initial Teaching Education</strong></p> <p>Commencing students must attempt the LANTITE in their first year of study and are required to successfully complete the LANTITE prior to undertaking their final Professional Experience Placement. </p> <p><strong>Course participation requirements</strong></p> <p>This course includes compulsory work placements. All students must meet the course’s <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/education/professional-experience/compliance">Safety in Practice Requirements</a> before their first placement. This includes external clearances to work with children and vulnerable people. The safety in practice requirements are completed separately to the course application.</p> </div>',
    apply_form = 'https://apply.utas.edu.au'
WHERE cricos_course_code = '070689D';

