UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Undergraduate Certificate in Climate Change Awareness and Action equips you with the foundational knowledge and skills to participate in efforts to mitigate and adapt to climate change, locally and globally. This certificate responds to that need.</div><p>You will study the type and magnitude of climate change impacts and possible responses, and build foundational skills in climate risk management. You will learn to facilitate climate-resilient planning and climate-related reporting requirements. Additionally, you will learn what to consider when planning for and managing climate impacts on future infrastructure and services. Upon completion of the certificate, you will be able to apply climate science knowledge to a range of human challenges, make linkages between sustainability and climate action, and use collaborative approaches to climate change problems and solutions.</p><p>This online course will prepare and inspire graduates for further educational opportunities and enhance their capacity to contribute to global efforts in climate change response. As a graduate, you will be equipped for a variety of climate change-related roles in industry and government. You will also meet entry criteria for multiple University of Tasmania courses at the Diploma and Bachelor levels.</p><p>As a graduate, you will be eligible to apply for credit or advanced standing for your studies towards degrees such as the Bachelor of Science (Sustainability) and the <a href="https://www.googleadservices.com/pagead/aclk?sa=L&amp;ai=DChcSEwjpz7SzwNeGAxXAFYMDHeB2BOIYABAAGgJzZg&amp;ase=2&amp;gclid=CjwKCAjwjqWzBhAqEiwAQmtgTzWVavzwkWFO1Yg9oHqZql92pnfS3-LRpussAJxrn5HmMfhn5lKfvhoChkEQAvD_BwE&amp;ei=dFVqZtrBCvj-g8UP7p-9gAU&amp;ohost=www.google.com&amp;cid=CAESVuD2SEqE_34XbTW8X489ARWxtO6XBtiAgADuJ33688tiIxQe5V4gvBKhhMDuJppRcFgDCbADsbPQuKHAEVkcriUHcSF5ofSxJ9FW3GeueImrkox-h6o0&amp;sig=AOD64_0lWAbUE3nTCWNmgw0lmghIsToK5g&amp;q&amp;sqi=2&amp;nis=4&amp;adurl&amp;ved=2ahUKEwjay6-zwNeGAxV4_6ACHe5PD1AQ0Qx6BAgGEAE">Diploma of Sustainable Living</a>. Certificate graduates may also receive credit into the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/k3s-bachelor-of-marine-and-antarctic-science">Bachelor of Marine and Antarctic Studies</a>, and the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p3j-bachelor-of-natural-environments-and-conservation">Bachelor of Natural Environments and Conservation</a>.</p><hr/><p><strong> Study without tuition fees in 2026 </strong></p><p><strong>For domestic students,</strong> the Undergraduate Certificate in Climate Change Awareness and Action is offered with <a href="#fees-scholarships">100% tuition fee scholarship</a> for students commencing in 2026. This means you pay <strong>NO tuition fees!</strong></p> </div>',
