course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Undergraduate Certificate in ICT Professional Practice provides a practical, skills-based introduction to the dynamic field of Information and Communication Technology.</div><p>Designed to help you develop relevant, up-to-date capabilities aligned with industry needs, the course strengthens your ability to contribute effectively in technical or support roles across a range of ICT areas. Whether you are looking to upskill, pivot into a new role, or enhance your career prospects, this course equips you with foundational knowledge and hands-on experience to take the next step in your ICT journey.</p><p>Led by experienced ICT academics, the teaching environment is designed to deliver distinctive, rewarding, and place-based learning experiences. It provides a student-centred and personal approach, helping you achieve your individual career goals.</p><p>On graduating from the Undergraduate Certificate in ICT Professional Practice, you may choose to build on your achievements and expand your skills and knowledge by continuing into <span style="box-sizing: border-box;">the<a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p1b-diploma-of-ict-professional-practice" target="_blank"> Diploma</a></span><a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p1b-diploma-of-ict-professional-practice"> of ICT Professional Practice</a> or the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p3t-bachelor-of-information-and-communication-technology">Bachelor of Information and Communication Technology,</a> with credit for the units you have already completed.</p><hr/><p><strong> Study without tuition fees in 2026 </strong></p><p><strong>For domestic students,</strong> the Undergraduate Certificate in ICT Professional Practice is offered with <a href="#fees-scholarships">100% tuition fee scholarship</a> for students commencing in 2026. This means you pay <strong>NO tuition fees!</strong></p> </div>',
