course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Professional industry certifications offer a credible, skills focused means of demonstrating your advanced competency with a particular sub discipline or technology. The value of professional certification to employers is high, and even for existing employees there is an ongoing need to maintain and build technical skills and knowledge.</div><p>The Undergraduate Certificate in ICT Professional Practice offers you the opportunity to gain relevant, up-to-date skills and globally recognised certifications that differentiate you and increase your employability. Industry certifications will also facilitate a rapid lateral move into a defined discipline within the ICT industry if you have experience in other fields.</p><p>Led and managed by ICT academics that have years of experience in delivering distinctive, rewarding, and place-based learning experiences, the teaching environment aims to provide a university experience that is student-centred and personal, enabling you to realise your individual career goals.</p><p>On graduation from the Undergraduate Certificate in ICT Professional Practice you may choose to build on your achievements and broaden your skills and knowledge further by continuing your study in the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p1b-diploma-of-ict-professional-practice">Diploma of ICT Professional Practice</a> or the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/cse/courses/p3t-bachelor-of-information-and-communication-technology">Bachelor of Information and Communication Technology</a> with credit for your units completed as part of the Certificate.</p><p>Commonwealth Supported Places are available for this course, see <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/bus/courses/z0l-undergraduate-certificate-in-agribusiness/_nocache#fees-and-scholarships">Fees &amp; scholarships</a> for more information.</p> </div>',
