UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede"><strong>This course is offered part-time only, over one year, or two semesters.</strong></div><p><strong>Become a digital health custodian</strong></p><p>Improve your skills, in clinical and non-clinical, support and administration.</p><p>The Graduate Certificate of Digital Health suits not only graduates of health, but those of science, data, digital, cyber security, public policy, human resources, humanities, and accounting and finance.</p><p>Prepare yourself for the forefront of healthcare innovation with our Graduate Certificate in Digital Health. Designed to meet the growing demand for skilled professionals in the dynamic health sector, this course equips you with evidence-based skills essential for success.</p><p>Digital technologies are now integral to daily life, and the world’s population has never been more interconnected. Innovation, particularly in the digital sphere, is happening at unprecedented scale. Even so, its application to improve the health of populations remains largely untapped, and there is immense scope for use of digital health solutions.</p><p>Increasingly, health workers are required to use their critical thinking to analyse data for the provision of health and care services. It is essential to understand the importance of trusted digital data to better connect service and care beyond one’s own role or organisation. This is applicable across all roles and settings, and is vital to the effective delivery and development of digital health solutions.</p><p>Throughout the course, you''ll study crictical areas such as health informatics, data security, and the transformative impact of digital systems on decision-making. You''ll gain invaluable experience navigating ethical, social, and economic considerations, ensuring you''re ready to lead in an ever-evolving industry. Position yourself at the intersection of technology and healthcare with our comprehensive Graduate Certificate in Digital Health.</p><p>As new technologies and opportunities emerge, those working in the health sector play a critical role in promoting and leading uptake of digital health solutions across the sector.</p> </div>',
