course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Accounting goes beyond number crunching. You''ll gain practical experience through internships and work with Tasmanian industries, building valuable connections for your future career.</div><p>The Master of Professional Accounting is perfect if you want to enter the field without formal qualifications or if you''re a professional looking to upskill. You''ll gain hands-on experience through internships, including opportunities at the Tax Clinic (available at the Hobart campus), and learn directly from industry experts.</p><p>A career in accounting involves expert consultation, helping businesses make informed decisions. You could find yourself providing financial advice to startups or working as a climate change accountant, offering sustainable solutions.</p><h4><strong>Key contacts</strong></h4><table border="1" style="width: 100%;"><tbody><tr><td> Current student enrolment questions and advice </td><td><a href="https://askus.utas.edu.au/app/answers/detail/a_id/1843/kw/uconnect">UConnect</a></td></tr><tr><td> Course Coordinator </td><td><a href="https://discover.utas.edu.au/mitali.panchal">Dr Mitali Panchal</a></td></tr></tbody></table><h4>Watch our webinar (International students)</h4><p>Senior Lecturer Dr Amrinder Khosa discusses how students can develop the advanced capabilities required to work in the professional accounting sector.</p><ul><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k4gPUHjkMwo">Watch now</a></li></ul> </div>',
