course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Take your academic journey further with an Honours degree.</div><p>An Honours Course is a one-year full-time program designed for high-achieving students who are ready to deepen their expertise and explore their passion through research. Honours combines advanced study with a significant research project in a chosen field. Whether you''re aiming to boost your employability, develop specialised analytical skills, or pave the way to a PhD, an Honours degree offers a powerful platform to elevate your academic and professional future.</p><p>The Bachelor of Environmental Design with Honours is for graduates of Bachelor-level degrees in Design or Architecture. Students in the program pursue their own projects under the supervision of academics in the School of Architecture and Design. Supervisors and projects must be agreed before completing applications. Study location, supervision parameters, and project type and outputs are all negotiated with supervisors in advance of commencement.</p> </div>',
