UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div style="border: 0px"><div class="lede">Explore educational research. Expand your impact.</div></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>The Bachelor of Education with Honours is a one-year full-time course (or part-time equivalent) designed for individuals with experience in educational contexts who are ready to deepen their understanding of teaching, learning, and education through research, while developing advanced, cross-disciplinary research skills.</p></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>This course welcomes applicants from a broad range of professional backgrounds—including schools, higher education, government, and non-government organisations. Whether you''re working in policy, community education, training, or advocacy, it offers a flexible and inclusive pathway to explore research in or about education.</p></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>Guided by a discipline-specific supervisor, you’ll undertake a self-directed research project tailored to your interests and aspirations. You’ll also join a diverse cohort of students from across the education sector, enriching your experience through collaborative dialogue and shared perspectives.</p></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>Designed with working professionals in mind, the course is delivered fully online and has no placement requirements, making it especially accessible for those balancing study with career commitments.</p></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>The Bachelor of Education with Honours provides a clear pathway to doctoral study (PhD or EdD) and serves as a strong foundation for careers in educational research, policy development, and advisory roles across both government and non-government settings.</p></div><div style="border: 0px"><p>Whether you''re passionate about improving classroom practice, shaping education policy, or investigating the social and cultural dimensions of learning, this course equips you with the tools to lead, influence, and innovate.</p></div> </div>',
    total_course_duration = 'Minimum 1 Year, up to a maximum of 3 years.',
    offshore_tuition_fee = '38950',
    entry_requirements = '',
    apply_form = 'https://apply.utas.edu.au'
WHERE cricos_course_code = 'UNKNOWN';

UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">This course provides you with an opportunity to engage in educational research while learning comprehensive in-depth and cross-disciplinary research skills. You will work closely with a discipline-specific supervisor to produce a self-directed research project and you’ll undertake units with small cross-disciplinary groups of students, adding breadth to your learning experience.</div><p>By the end of the Bachelor of Education with Honours, you will have specialist knowledge in an area of Education Studies as well as advanced knowledge of research design and methods. You will be able to investigate and evaluate an issue, problem or phenomenon in Education, and design and implement independent research to effect change. You will develop skills of educational research and theoretical inquiry in the design and implementation of a significant project while broadening your research skill set.</p><p>We recognise that relationships are fundamental to effective teaching and that the past experiences of students contribute to their capacity for learning. The Bachelor of Education with Honours is taught in flexible mode using adult education principles that value students’ experiences and enables learning in online environments and via one-on-one supervision. This course provides a clear one year full time pathway to PhD or EdD eligibility, and provides an excellent foundation for employment in research-related and policy roles in government and non-government organisations.</p> </div>',
