UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Graduate Certificate of Early Childhood Education will prepare you to lead early learning experiences for children from birth to 8 years of age.</div><p>Your studies will embed indigenous worldviews, education for sustainability, and health and wellbeing. You’ll learn to recognise how relationships with self, others, cultures, and places are critical to teaching and learning with children. Graduates are inclusive education practitioners with specific capacities to lead with play-based pedagogies, and to work with complex communities.</p><p>The Graduate Certificate aims to develop informed practitioners who are equipped to respond to opportunities and challenges in a range of formal and informal early learning context . It is underpinned by a strong research-practice nexus and is guided by our commitment to social justice as a core value for the work educators do.</p><p>The Graduate Certificate of Early Childhood Education is a professional nationally accredited qualification for leading early learning experiences for children birth to 8 years. It prepares graduates for recruitment in local, interstate, and international school systems, as well as in early childhood and care settings.</p><p>By experiencing a curriculum that aligns with the Early Years Learning Framework and the standards of the Australian Children’s Education and Care Quality Framework, and that embeds indigenous worldviews, education for sustainability, and health and wellbeing, our students come to recognise that relationships with self, others, cultures, and place are critical to teaching and learning with children.</p><p>Our aim is to graduate inclusive education practitioners with specific capacities to lead with play-based pedagogies, and to work with complex communities characterised by geographical isolation, social inequality, and a high incidence of trauma.</p><p>If you don''t meet the eligibility requirements, the combined early education option may be for you. Complete the Bachelor Of Education (primary) together with the Graduate Certificate in Early Childhood, <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/education" title="Education">explore your options</a>.</p><hr/><h5>Watch our course information webinar</h5><p>Thinking of studying this course and want to learn more? This webinar explores course structures, career opportunities, and the student experience to support your study journey.</p><p><a href="https://youtu.be/vliK5mk7gmk?si=KUqlzg5P9Ww-60I-" target="_blank" title="Watch our webinar">Watch now</a></p> </div>',
