UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Turn your passion into a profession: inspire future generations as a teacher</div><p>Transform your existing Bachelor''s degree into a rewarding teaching career. This path allows you to turn your passion into a meaningful profession, whether you''re seeking a more fulfilling career, greater work-life balance, or the opportunity to positively impact the next generation. By becoming a teacher, you can use your expertise to inspire, engage, and make a lasting difference in your students'' lives, all while enjoying a career that offers stability and opportunities for personal growth.</p><h6>Why choose the Master of Teaching?</h6><p>By pursuing a Master of Teaching, you’ll gain the skills and knowledge to teach in a primary or secondary school setting. This pre-service teaching degree builds on your tertiary qualifications and experience, enabling you to complete a teaching qualification.</p><ul><li><strong>Choose your teaching stream:</strong> Specialise in either primary or secondary teaching to align with your interests and career goals.</li><li><strong>Informed by research:</strong> Your studies are guided by internationally renowned research in areas like English literacy, inclusive education, arts and creativity, and regional and rural education.</li><li><strong>Professional accreditation:</strong> Accredited by the Tasmanian Teachers Registration Board, this course is recognised across all Australian states and territories.</li><li><strong>Hands-on experience:</strong> Complete 60 days of professional experience placements in classrooms, helping you graduate with the confidence to inspire the next generation.</li><li><strong>Flexible support:</strong> Take advantage of a range of scholarships and study options designed to fit your life. Whether you prefer part-time or full-time study, online or on campus, you can tailor your learning to suit your lifestyle and commitments.</li></ul><h6>Specialisation options</h6><table class="table table__full" id="table52747" summary="Specialisations"><thead><tr><th id="table52747r1c1"> Primary Proficiencies (Prep to Grade 6)</th><th id="table52747r1c2"> Secondary Specialisations (Grades 7 to 12)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> English </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> English </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Humanities and Social Sciences </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> Humanities and Social Sciences </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Mathematics </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> Mathematics </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Science </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> Science </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> The Arts (Drama, Music, Visual or Media arts) </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> The Arts (Drama, Music, Visual or Media arts) </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Languages </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> Languages </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Health and Physical Education </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> - </td></tr><tr><td headers="table52747r1c1"> Technologies </td><td headers="table52747r1c2"> - </td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Note: If you select a secondary teaching specialisation you''ll choose two curriculum teaching areas, which are determined by the Major or Specialisation undertaken in your undergraduate degree.</em></p><h6>Commonwealth Teaching Scholarships</h6><p>If you’re starting your teaching journey, you could be eligible for up to $40,000 from the Australian Government to support your studies. This incredible opportunity is part of the Commonwealth Teaching Scholarships Program, designed to attract high-achieving and passionate individuals.</p><ul><li>Supports both undergraduate and postgraduate students in initial teacher education (ITE) programs.</li><li>Helps cover study costs in exchange for teaching in government schools or early learning settings for a period equivalent to your course length.</li><li>Up to 1,000 scholarships available annually from 2024 to 2028.</li></ul><p>Apply now at <a href="https://www.education.gov.au/teaching-scholarships" rel="external" target="_blank">education.gov.au/teaching-scholarships</a></p><p>For other university scholarships, visit our <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/scholarships-fees-and-costs">scholarships page</a>.</p><hr/><h6><strong>Watch our course information webinar</strong></h6><p>Thinking of studying this course and want to learn more? This webinar explores course structures, career opportunities, and the student experience to support your study journey.</p><p><a href="https://youtu.be/vliK5mk7gmk?si=KUqlzg5P9Ww-60I-" target="_blank" title="Watch our webinar">Watch now</a></p> </div>',
