course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">If you are a registered nurse looking to expand your career to Midwifery, the Graduate Diploma of Midwifery will prepare you to make that transition. This accredited full time course will equip you with the knowledge, clinical skills, professional values and capabilities needed to provide safe, compassionate and evidence-informed care to women, newborns and families across a variety of settings.</div><p style="border: 0px">Throughout your studies, you will engage in a dynamic blended learning environment which combines online study, face-to-face intensive workshops. You need to have access to clinical practice in midwifery for the duration of the course; this means you must have concurrent employment minimum 0.6 FTE in a Midwifery Unit to be able to complete your midwifery practice experience. You will engage in the full spectrum of midwifery practice, from pregnancy and birth to postnatal support and family partnership. The course is built around woman-centred and culturally responsive care, public health, ethical principles, and sustainability—ensuring you not only learn what you need for today but are also equipped for the evolving future of maternity care.</p><p style="border: 0px">When you successfully complete the Graduate Diploma of Midwifery, you will be eligible to apply for registration as a Midwife through the Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency (Ahpra). You will graduate ready to make a meaningful contribution to maternity services, advocate for social justice, and influence positive change in healthcare.</p> </div>',
