UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">This course has been replaced by the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/chm/courses/h7m-master-of-advanced-nursing-specialisation?year=2026" title="Master of Advanced Nursing (Specialisation) (H7M)">Master of Advanced Nursing (Specialisation)</a>. For all 2026 applications, please visit that course page.</div><hr/><p>Specialist skills and knowledge to advance your nursing career</p><p>Whether you’re in the early stages of your career and wanting to further develop your clinical expertise, or moving into a role that encourages you to lead and manage, our postgraduate nursing courses and wide range of specialisations will support your goals and ambitions.</p><p>This course is the final step in the postgraduate clinical nursing journey, and provides you with a unique opportunity for developing a complex and integrated body of knowledge specifically designed for clinical nurses.</p><p>Your capabilities will be developed in areas including clinical governance, leadership and how this advances healthcare change, implementation science, and the dissemination of advanced clinical knowledge such as writing for publication. This advanced knowledge and skill is eminently suited to supporting you in your current role, and advancing your nursing career.</p><p>The Master of Clinical Nursing articulates directly from the Bachelor of Nursing with Professional Honours or Graduate Diploma courses and consists of 2 x 25 credit point units. You must have completed a Graduate Diploma or equivalent for entry into the course.</p><h4>Health partner scholarships</h4><p>To help you advance your career, generous scholarships are available for the graduate certificate and graduate diploma units of the masters program to employees of our valued industry partners. <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/partners/health" title="Health partner scholarships">Search for your employer</a>, speak to your workplace, or