UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">A research degree is an advanced study program that gives you an opportunity to deeply explore a topic with the support and expertise of your supervisors. An extensive range of projects are available from which to select; please see the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees/available-projects">Available Projects</a> page to explore our Higher Degree by Research projects.</div><p>Research degree students are driven by curiosity and creativity and have a passion to solve problems and advance humanity. As a PhD student, you will conduct independent research in a specialised field and generate new knowledge that makes a positive difference in and beyond your chosen field.</p><p>PhD students benefit from training activities and career development opportunities to develop high-level research, communication and project management skills. The knowledge and skills obtained from a PhD will set you up for success for a wide range of future career opportunities.</p><p><strong>Location</strong>: our courses are available on all campuses</p><p><strong>Australian Qualification Framework level</strong>: 10</p><p><strong>Scholarships and Fees</strong>: For information on available Scholarships and Fees please visit <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees/scholarships-and-fees">https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees/scholarships-and-fees</a></p><p><strong>Entry Requirements: </strong>To learn more about Entry Requirements and Research Degrees visit <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees/what-is-a-research-degree">https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees/what-is-a-research-degree</a></p><p><strong>How to apply</strong>: <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees">https://www.utas.edu.au/research/degrees</a></p><p><strong>Want to find a supervisor</strong>: <a href="https://discover.utas.edu.au/">https://discover.utas.edu.au/</a></p> </div>',
