UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Diploma of Counselling is an introductory course that provides you with the skills to understand human behaviour.</div><p>You will explore a range of topics, including mental health, the impact of chronic health conditions on quality of life, foundational mental health intervention skills, and applied counselling skills. During your studies, you will focus on adopting healthy thoughts and behaviours as part of a self-care approach. This will introduce you to a range of skills to manage stress and enhance the well-being of yourself and others through lifestyle practices, mindfulness, and positive psychology.</p><p>The Diploma of Counselling can be undertaken for a variety of reasons: as a complementary skillset to support an existing career, by people managers looking to support their staff, or to build an understanding of mental health to support yourself and others.</p><p>If you''re interested in further study, you can progress with credit into the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/53f" title="Bachelor of Psychological Science">Bachelor of Psychological Science</a> to continue your journey in the study of psychology and counselling.</p><p>If you''re interested in becoming a qualified counsellor you will need to complete the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/courses/chm/courses/m6i-graduate-diploma-in-counselling">Graduate Diploma of Counselling.</a></p><p>Graduates may meet the requirements for registration with the ACA as a professional member. There may be additional requirements for registration beyond the completion of the course. For further registration requirements, please visit the <a href="http://www.theaca.net.au">Australian Counselling Association</a> website.</p><p>If you have any queries about the accreditation process, please <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/enquire">contact us</a> for further information.</p><h3><strong>Explore Your Future in Psychology &amp; Counselling</strong></h3><p>Are you curious about where your studies in Psychology and Counselling could take you next?</p><p>View the webinar to discover pathways for further study and professional development. Whether you''re aiming to become a school counsellor, clinical psychologist, or simply want to enhance your counselling skills, this will answer your questions.</p><p>You''ll learn more about your pathways into studying Psychology and Counselling. Covering course information and entry requirements for:</p><ul><li>Bachelor of Psychological Sciences (Honours)​</li><li>Master of Professional Psychology ​</li><li>Master of Psychology (Clinical)​</li><li>Graduate Certificate and Graduate Diploma of Counselling</li></ul><p><a class="button button--action" href="https://youtu.be/EsOMzqERUaM">View the webinar here</a></p> </div>',
