course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Remote and extreme environments push the boundaries of healthcare delivery and demand professionals who are ready to rise to the challenge. The Graduate Certificate of Healthcare in Remote and Extreme Environments is your gateway to the essentials of healthcare in some of the world’s most demanding conditions.</div><p><br/>Tailored for doctors, nurses, paramedics, and allied health professionals, this course offers a foundation in the principles and practices of remote and extreme environment healthcare. You’ll gain the skills to plan, organise, and deliver care in settings where resources are limited, conditions are harsh, and adaptability is key.</p><p><br/>Built for busy professionals, the course is delivered online and part-time, giving you the flexibility to study while continuing your career. You’ll also have the opportunity to take part in practical and residential units that bring learning to life through simulation and hands-on experience.</p><p><br/>Whether you''re just beginning your journey into remote healthcare or looking to expand your scope, this certificate offers a dynamic and multidisciplinary launchpad to make a meaningful impact where it matters most.</p> </div>',
