course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Graduate Certificate of Counselling is designed to train graduates who will be able to address the mental health needs of Tasmania and beyond.</div><p>This course equips students with fundamental knowledge and skills in counselling, together with an understanding of the ethical, legal and professional issues in relation to the practice of counselling required for employment in a range of counselling roles.</p><p>The course is also a professional development opportunity for people already working in counselling roles within their workplace.</p><p>Students will develop an understanding of the social, cultural and developmental context in which counselling occurs and of a range of therapeutic approaches and appropriate to a range of client ages, needs and circumstances. The course also aims to provide professional development opportunities for people working in counselling roles.</p><h6>Are you curious about where your studies in Psychology and Counselling could take you next?</h6><p>View the webinar to discover pathways for further study and professional development. Whether you''re aiming to become a school counsellor, clinical psychologist, or simply want to enhance your counselling skills, this will answer your questions.</p><p>You''ll learn more about your pathways into studying Psychology and Counselling. Covering course information and entry requirements for:</p><ul><li>Bachelor of Psychological Sciences (Honours)​</li><li>Master of Professional Psychology ​</li><li>Master of Psychology (Clinical)​</li><li>Graduate Certificate and Graduate Diploma of Counselling</li></ul><p><a class="button button--action" href="https://youtu.be/EsOMzqERUaM">View the webinar here</a></p> </div>',
