course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">When you study the Master of Professional Psychology you will be taught primarily by practicing psychologists who are focused on preparing you to step into this exclusive profession with confidence. Throughout the course you will have opportunities to build relationships with your teachers and peers, meaning you can build your professional networks before you even graduate.</div><p>Our approach is fully built around a community-focused, scientist-practitioner model, with an ungraded-pass methodology that focusses on collegiality, competency development, and a genuine depth and breadth of learning that builds confidence and competence in the profession of psychology practice.</p><p>When you study with us, you receive regular mentorship, collaborative learning, and a dynamic support network not as a student, but as an early career colleague, as we are dedicated to your success.</p><p>As the national leader in program-wide Objective Structured Clinical Examinations (OSCE), you will have opportunities throughout your learning to practice your skills in the moment.</p><p>On successful completion of the Master of Professional Psychology, graduates will be eligible to undertake a sixth year (the +1 year) of supervised practice. The one-year supervised practice internship is organised between a graduate and their employer, with approval by the <a href="https://r.search.yahoo.com/_ylt=Awr98Iigqe1o54EA_QML5gt.;_ylu=Y29sbwNncTEEcG9zAzIEdnRpZAMEc2VjA3Ny/RV=2/RE=1761615521/RO=10/RU=https%3a%2f%2fwww.ahpra.gov.au%2fdocuments%2fdefault.aspx%3frecord%3dWD25%252F34714%26dbid%3dAP%26chksum%3ddMK92S%252FYnUT%252FQXh53Q%252FEtw%253D%253D/RK=2/RS=PKrJWnoY_LvDTsFIXVQwUpixO6c-" title="https://r.search.yahoo.com/_ylt=Awr98Iigqe1o54EA_QML5gt.;_ylu=Y29sbwNncTEEcG9zAzIEdnRpZAMEc2VjA3Ny/RV=2/RE=1761615521/RO=10/RU=https%3a%2f%2fwww.ahpra.gov.au%2fdocuments%2fdefault.aspx%3frecord%3dWD25%252F34714%26dbid%3dAP%26chksum%3ddMK92S%252FYnUT%252FQ">Psychology Board of Australia</a>, and leads to general registration as a psychologist, with approval by the Psychology Board of Australia.</p><p><strong>For International students only</strong></p><p>A student visa will cover the duration of your Master''s program only. To undertake the additional one year of supervised practice, you will be required to apply for a different visa subclass to lawfully remain in Australia during that period. It is strongly recommended that you consult a registered migration agent to obtain professional advice regarding your visa options and application process.</p><p><strong>Our Island is your campus</strong></p><p>You will learn about the many factors influencing mental health outcomes in our community so that you can facilitate safe and inclusive clinical psychology practice. We aim to tailor your research projects and placement experiences to your area(s) of interest. We offer placements across the public, private and community not-for-profit sectors, including community and private clinics, forensic services, education settings, and hospitals, supporting you to align your learning experience with your passions and aspirations.</p><p>The culturally safe and inclusive skills, knowledge, and confidence you build during this course will help you to provide vital support to local communities.</p> </div>',
