UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Master of Dementia offers a research-enabled, cross-disciplinary understanding of dementia and its impact on individuals, societies and governments. Graduates will possess a range of knowledge and perspectives, and deep insights to the nature and quality of evidence which underpins them, to inform their professional and personal support for the needs of people with dementia. Experience in critical appraisal and design of research allows graduates to choose the best information and evidence, or to design research where the evidence is lacking. As expectations increase around person-centred care, and decision making informed by a deep knowledge of dementia, a variety of leadership and design opportunities may become available for those with postgraduate qualifications in dementia.</div><hr/><h4>The Wicking Dementia Centre</h4><p><a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/wicking">The Wicking Dementia Research and Education Centre</a> is at the forefront of translational research of relevance to people with dementia and their carers, and provides a range of innovative educational programs on dementia. The Wicking Dementia Centre undertakes multidisciplinary research around three main themes – the <strong>Care, Cause and Prevention</strong> of Dementia. Educational programs are closely interlinked with the Centre’s research programs.</p> </div>',
