UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Healthcare in remote and extreme environments requires clinical competence, leadership, and the ability to adapt and innovate under pressure. The Master of Healthcare in Remote and Extreme Environments is designed for experienced professionals ready to take their expertise to the next level and make a lasting impact in the world’s most challenging settings.</div><p>This course is ideally suited to doctors, nurses, paramedics, and allied health professionals from diverse backgrounds who want to expand their skills and knowledge to include advanced healthcare delivery in remote and extreme environments. You will further develop your ability to plan, organise, and deliver care in these contexts, while enjoying the flexibility to study online and part-time alongside your professional commitments.</p><p>You’ll also have the opportunity to enhance your learning through elective units with residential and practical components, including simulation and hands-on experiences that bring your studies to life. In your final year, you’ll choose between two capstone pathways: a research project that allows you to explore a specialised area of interest, or a workplace-based portfolio that demonstrates your mastery in real-world settings.</p><p>Whether you''re aiming to lead in expedition medicine, humanitarian response, military healthcare, or remote community practice, this course offers a transformative experience that empowers you to deliver exceptional care where it’s needed most.</p> </div>',
