course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Bachelor of Design has been completely reimagined around the transformative theme of regeneration. In this degree, you’ll explore design’s next evolution, where creativity meets sustainability and innovation drives positive change.</div><p>You’ll build strong technical, creative, and strategic skills while learning how design connects with real-world challenges such as climate adaptation, health futures, and social innovation. Whether you’re creating circular systems for waste reduction, designing experiences that improve wellbeing, or developing new materials from local resources, you’ll graduate ready to design solutions that work better for people and the planet.</p><p>Through the Regenerative Design Accelerator core subjects, you’ll learn how design can be applied across disciplines to address complex challenges and support innovation. In the Design Practices Major, you’ll take part in hands-on studio learning that connects traditional design skills with emerging approaches to sustainability, collaboration, and systems design.</p><p>Your learning is structured around three key pillars:</p><ul><li>Design Foundations, which develops your technical and visual design skills;</li><li>Collaborative and Social Practice, where you learn to design with communities for meaningful change; and</li><li>Systems and Futures, where you explore circular and regenerative approaches that prepare you for the future of design.</li></ul><p>You’ll also benefit from Tasmania’s distinctive place-based learning environment, collaborating with local communities, industries, and festivals to apply your skills in real contexts while developing insights that can be transferred globally.</p><p>The Bachelor of Design offers flexible study options. You can:</p><ul><li>Study the Bachelor of Design as a standalone degree and complete it in just three years, building a strong foundation for a career in design.</li><li>Complete a double major with <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/science#sustainability" target="_blank">Sustainability</a> and finish your degree in just three years.</li><li>Choose a <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/undergraduate/double-degrees" target="_blank">double degree</a>, combining Design with another discipline such as Science, Business, or ICT, and graduate with two qualifications in four years.</li></ul><h6>Catalyst Program</h6><p>Want to combine your degree with overseas trips, summer research programs, scholarships and special events? Our Catalyst Program offers domestic high achieving school leavers all this and more.</p><p>All domestic students with an ATAR of 90 or greater, enrolled in a range of STEM courses will be awarded a $3,000 Catalyst Scholarship. Across the program, students can access scholarships of up to $14,500 in value, and gain experience that will make you stand out in your chosen field.</p><p><a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/catalyst-program">Learn more about the Catalyst Program</a></p><h6>Half Year Periods</h6><p>Half Year Periods run just before Semester 1 and 2. Two Design intensives – <em data-end="968" data-start="942">Circular Design Thinking</em> and <em data-end="998" data-start="973">Regenerative Innovation</em> – take place in these weeks, so you’ll start your studies early with a hands-on design sprint.</p><hr/><h6><strong>Ready to explore your study options?</strong></h6><p>Book an online one-on-one appointment with our course coordinator to discuss any course-related questions and explore how the Bachelor of Design can support your study and career goals.</p><p><a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/BachelorofDesign@UniversityTasmania.onmicrosoft.com/" title="Book now">Book now</a></p> </div>',
