UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede"> This combined degree brings together scientific curiosity and engineering innovation, giving you the tools to understand our changing world and design solutions that shape a more sustainable future.</div><p data-end="718" data-start="370"> In science, you will explore the building blocks of life, the environment, and the universe through hands-on learning and discovery. Whether you are drawn to climate science, biology, chemistry, or physical and mathematical sciences, you will develop critical thinking skills and a deep understanding of how science can inform real-world decisions.</p><p data-end="1037" data-start="720"> This complements your studies in Climate Safe Engineering, where you will gain practical skills to apply that knowledge through purposeful design and problem solving. This approach embeds climate mitigation and adaptation into every aspect of engineering. You will learn to create systems, technologies, and infrastructure that are not only efficient and effective, but also safe for people and the planet.</p><p data-end="1332" data-start="1039"> At the University of Tasmania, you will learn from and within one of the world''s most extraordinary environments. Tasmania is your living laboratory, where ancient landscapes, unique ecosystems, and real-world climate challenges provide endless opportunities for applied learning and research.</p><p data-end="1591" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="1334"> Together, these two degrees allow you to cross disciplines and build a unique skillset that is increasingly sought after. You will graduate as a scientist and an engineer, prepared to investigate the challenges of today and create the solutions of tomorrow.</p><h6>Catalyst Program</h6><p>Want to combine your degree with overseas trips, summer research programs, scholarships and special events? Our Catalyst Program offers domestic high achieving school leavers all this and more.</p><p>All domestic students with an ATAR of 90 or greater, enrolled in a range of STEM courses will be awarded a $3,000 Catalyst Scholarship. Across the program students can access scholarships of up to $14,500 in value, and gain experience that will make you stand out in your chosen field. <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/catalyst-program">Learn more about the Catalyst Program</a>.</p><h6>PRIMED Program</h6><p>The Profession Ready Industry Merged Engineering Degree (<a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/about/news-and-stories/articles/2022/engineers-primed-to-be-more-sustainable-and-job-ready" target="_blank">PRIMED</a>) program is an integral part of educating new engineers at UTAS. With a strong focus on preparing students for the workforce, PRIMED fosters active participation of practicing professional engineers in educating the next generation of engineering professionals. Through PRIMED, you will engage with professional engineers in various ways, including classroom activities and immersive field experiences like site visits, workshops, design challenges, and work placements.</p><hr/><h5>Watch our course information webinar</h5><p>Thinking of studying this course and want to learn more? This webinar explores course structures, career opportunities, and the student experience to support your study journey.</p><p><a href="https://youtu.be/fVqYpH2Da2c?si=X0x06970a-mHDD4d" target="_blank" title="Watch our webinar">Watch now</a></p> </div>',
