UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Family history is for everybody. We all have stories in our family tree waiting to be told.</div><p>The Diploma of Family History will give you essential knowledge and tools to bring the past to life through tracing your family experiences and understanding the historical forces that shaped them.</p><p>Develop the skills and knowledge to share family stories with others. Our Family History course is designed to help you explore your family''s past, while also becoming more proficient and comfortable in a digital environment. You''ll learn how to undertake historical research while developing your communication and writing skills. Plus, you''ll be part of a supportive cohort of family history enthusiasts and experts.<br/><br/>Each unit is taught by specialists in Australian, British, European and Asian histories. As you progress through your course you’ll learn how to research, write and creatively communicate family history. You''ll also develop skills to identify, analyse and interpret historical information from a range of family history sources.</p><p>You''ll learn how to use oral history, family heirlooms and photographs, as well as physical and digital archives to illuminate your family’s past. The Diploma of Family History focuses on understanding individual lives in their wider historical contexts, through investigating the impacts of events such as war, convict transportation, and migration.</p><p>Our Family History courses are fully online. You can study these units in any order you choose, but we recommend commencing your course with Introduction to Family History. Many students study one unit per term.</p><p><strong>In 2026, our dates will be:</strong></p><p><strong>Term 1</strong>: 2 Feb – 29 Mar 2026</p><p><strong>Term 2</strong>: 4 May – 28 Jun 2026</p><p><strong>Term 3</strong>: 27 Jul – 20 Sep 2026</p><p><strong>Term 4</strong>: 19 Oct –13 Dec 2026</p><p>________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p><p><strong>2026 Society of Genealogists Scholarship</strong></p><p>This scholarship is to support a student to study the Diploma of Family History.</p><p>The scholarship will cover the full tuition of the 8 units.</p><p>To be eligible a student must be commencing the Diploma of Family History in Term 1, 2026 and enrolling in the Introduction to Family History. To be considered students must be a current member of the <a href="https://www.sag.org.au">Society of Australian Genealogists</a>.</p><p>Applications close 01 December 2025</p><p><a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/study/scholarships-fees-and-costs/domestic-scholarships/a-z?code=SCH_SAG">Read more and apply</a></p><p>________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p> </div>',
