course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">The Bachelor of Arts with Honours is a specialised one-year course designed to deepen your understanding and research capabilities in a chosen field within the Humanities, Social Sciences, Creative Arts and Media, or the study of Geography and Environment.</div><p>You will engage with advanced theory and research methods to explore social and cultural issues of both local and global relevance, developing into an independent, critical, and reflective thinker.</p><p>Throughout the course, you will work closely with an academic supervisor to design and manage an independent research project aligned with your interests. This culminates in a dissertation that allows you to investigate a topic in depth and demonstrate your expertise.</p><p>By the end you will have gained advanced skills in research, analysis, and communication, preparing you for postgraduate study, such as a Master of Arts or PhD, or for a wide range of professional careers.</p><p>Whether you''re aiming to boost your employability, develop specialised analytical skills, or pave the way to a PhD, an Honours degree offers a powerful platform to elevate your academic and professional future.</p><div class="g-row g-row__pad-md"><div class="g-col-global-1-2 g-col-sm-1-1"><div class="richtext richtext__medium"></div></div></div> </div>',
