course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede"><strong>Take your academic journey further with an Honours degree.</strong></div><p>An honours year is a one-year (full time) up to three-year (full time) course designed for high-achieving students who are ready to deepen their expertise and explore their passion through research. Honours combines advanced study with a significant research project in your chosen field. Whether you''re aiming to boost your employability, develop specialised analytical skills, or pave the way to a PhD, an honours degree offers a powerful platform to elevate your academic and professional future.</p><p>This honours course will prepare you for roles in agricultural research organisations, agribusiness, and higher degree research. Taught by the <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/tia">Tasmanian Institute of Agriculture (TIA)</a>, you’ll be learning at the cutting edge of agriculture, guided by world-leading research and strong industry connections.</p><p>Curious about the kinds of projects you could work on? From soil health and crop protection to dairy cow welfare and precision agriculture, explore the range of research opportunities at <a href="https://www.utas.edu.au/tia/study/honours">Honours Opportunities in TIA</a> and discover where your interests could take you. .</p><p>The course provides an entry point into honours for students who have completed science-based degrees other than the Bachelor of Agricultural Science.</p> </div>',
