course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Are you passionate about making a difference and contributing to the sustainability of food and fibre production? The Undergraduate Certificate in Agribusiness is your opportunity to explore Australia''s agriculture industry and take the first steps towards running a successful agricultural-based business.</div><p>You''ll gain commercial awareness and insight into agribusiness industries. You''ll explore the importance of management planning in agribusiness and learn how managers integrate planning outputs into business operations. Developed in consultation with industry experts like Mike Badcock from Enchanted Isle Farms and Terry Brient from the Tasmanian Agriculture Productivity Group, the course offers practical skills through real-world case studies, ensuring you can apply what you learn directly in the workplace.</p><p>This course is an excellent foundation for anyone looking to enter the agriculture industry or as a stepping stone for current agricultural professionals aiming to advance their careers.</p><hr/><p><strong> Study without tuition fees in 2026 </strong></p><p><strong>For domestic students,</strong> the Undergraduate Certificate in Agribusiness is offered with <a href="#fees-scholarships">100% tuition fee scholarship</a> for students commencing in 2026. This means you pay <strong>NO tuition fees!</strong></p> </div>',
