UPDATE courses SET
course_description = '<div class="richtext richtext__medium"> <div class="lede">Want to work in an industry that has huge growth potential and an ever-expanding scope? Choosing a career within the technology sector will put you at the forefront of innovation.</div><p>The Undergraduate Certificate in Applied Technologies provides you with hands-on experience with real-world industry issues like setting up automation, handling information security and analysing data for cyber security. You’ll also learn the principles of designing and building programs using the Python language, explore how computer networks are setup and customised for different industry needs, and learn how data management software can improve decision making and communication in your workplace.</p><p>Advancing technologies over the past decade have significantly transformed production, manufacturing and communication in every sector of the economy. In fact, it''s projected that demand for technology workers will grow by 100,000 between 2024 and 2027*. Developed in consultation with industry experts, the Undergraduate Certificate in Applied Technologies is designed to give you the latest skills and knowledge to hit the ground running as you enter Australia’s booming technology industry.</p><hr/><p><strong> Study without tuition fees in 2026 </strong></p><p><strong>For domestic students,</strong> the Undergraduate Certificate in Applied Technologies is offered with <a href="#fees-scholarships">100% tuition fee scholarship</a> for students commencing in 2026. This means you pay <strong>NO tuition fees!</strong></p> </div>',
